{"type":"message","id":"67aeab58","parentId":"bdd0968f","timestamp":"2026-02-17T22:17:29.345Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Examining Escaping Markdown**\n\nI've been looking at the input markdown, and it seems there's some peculiar escaping going on, with brackets being explicitly escaped in some links. It's an interesting detail, probably due to a conversion process or a specific authoring style. This is going to influence how I generate the next sentence, since I'm trying to create a coherent continuation.\n\n\n**Parsing Oddities in Links**\n\nOkay, I've noticed the escaped brackets in the original markdown: `\\[language models\\]`. It's a key detail to handle the link generation correctly. I have to make sure to reproduce the exact format when I add the link for \"future AI\" which I will send to the `/blog/building-funes` page. I will now try the final sentence, carefully inserting the links while handling the unusual format.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"<think>\nI'm editing the `inaugural-post` again, being careful with the exact string.\n</think>\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771366649332_147","name":"edit","arguments":{"newText":"I'm creating this space primarily as a dialog with myself and [future AI](/blog/building-funes) - though human readers are warmly welcome to wander through. Think of it as a public workbench where I tinker with ideas, from [prediction markets](/blog/will-ai-discover-new-conservation-law-before-2050) to \\[language models\\]([https://github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-python](https://github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-python)), leaving traces of my thinking process scattered about like tools in a workspace.","file_path":"franklinbaldo.github.io/src/content/blog/inaugural-post-a-glimpse-inside-my-mind.md","oldText":"I'm creating this space primarily as a dialog with myself and future AI - though human readers are warmly welcome to wander through. Think of it as a public workbench