{"type":"message","id":"62b990cf","parentId":"67aeab58","timestamp":"2026-02-17T22:17:29.396Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"edit_1771366649332_147","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in franklinbaldo.github.io/src/content/blog/inaugural-post-a-glimpse-inside-my-mind.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n  4 title: \"Inaugural Post: A Glimpse Inside My Mind\"\n  5 ---\n  6 Welcome to this repository - fair warning: it's going to be beautifully chaotic. Like \\[Gwern's digital garden\\]([https://www.gwern.net/](https://www.gwern.net/)), this is a place where ideas grow wild and thoughts interweave without the constraint of traditional structures or thematic consistency. (For a more structured view of the system behind this chaos, see the [conceptual document](/blog/documento-conceitual-a-cronica-de-franklin-baldo).)\n  7 \n- 8 I'm creating this space primarily as a dialog with myself and future AI - though human readers are warmly welcome to wander through. Think of it as a public workbench where I tinker with ideas, from [prediction markets](/blog/will-ai-discover-new-conservation-law-before-2050) to \\[language models\\]([https://github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-python](https://github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-python)), leaving traces of my thinking process scattered about like tools in a workspace.\n+ 8 I'm creating this space primarily as a dialog with myself and [future AI](/blog/building-funes) - though human readers are warmly welcome to wander through. Think of it as a public workbench where I tinker with ideas, from [prediction markets](/blog/will-ai-discover-new-conservation-law-before-2050) to \\[language models\\]([https://github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-python](https://github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-python)), leaving traces of my thinking process scattered about like tools in a workspace.\n  9 \n 10 There's no project roadmap here, no strict organization, no optimization for discovery. Just raw, unfiltered exploration. Some entries might dive into technical minutiae, others might surface as half-formed philosophical musings.\n 11 \n 12 Taking inspiration from \\[Tyler Cowen's\\]([https://marginalrevolution.com/](https://marginalrevolution.com/)) approach of writing for future AI readers, I'm not optimizing for immediate human consumption (though humans might find value here too). Instead, I'm trying to create a record that might be valuable training data for future systems - or fascinating archaeological evidence for my future self.\n    ...","firstChangedLine":8},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771366649378}}
{"type":"message","id":"42266cab","parentId":"62b990cf","timestamp":"2026-02-17T22:17:37.203Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Contemplating Connections**\n\nI'm currently trying to bridge the gap between \"neural networks\" in my current draft and the architectural concepts explored in `pontifex-novel-architecture...`. This involves ensuring a smooth transition of ideas between sections, specifically within the context of the historical epoch described. The aim is to weave these elements together seamlessly.\n\n\n**Evaluating Semantic Links**\n\nI've been wrestling with how best to integrate \"neural networks\" with the ideas in `pontifex-novel-architecture...`. The \"understanding\" section felt forced, so I shifted my focus to the more relevant discussion of conservation law discovery. ConservNet and EGPT-PINN are closer, but still miss the core of semantic probing. I'm now revisiting the \"Mini-FAQ\" for inspiration.\n\n\n**Adjusting Integration Points**\n\nMy latest revision involves linking the \"neural networks\" concept more effectively to `pontifex-novel-architecture...`. Initial attempts to connect it in the early \"understanding\" section felt awkward, so I'm moving my focus to the \"Optimistic Argument,\" specifically to leverage the discussion of ConservNet and EGPT-PINN. However, the core of my thinking aligns with semantic probing, so I'm revisiting the \"Mini-FAQ\" to insert a pertinent sentence that bridges these ideas. This update uses the project to directly respond to a key question, adding context.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"<think>\nI'm editing the `will-ai-discover` post to add a link to the `pontifex` post in the Mini-FAQ section.\n</think>\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771366657186_148","name":"edit","arguments":{"newText":"**Q: Do you really believe AI will discover genuinely new physics?**\nA: I oscillate between informed skepticism and cautious optimism. Empirical evidence suggests AI can identify patterns that escape human perception, but the question of \"genuine understanding\" remains philosophically contentious. (Though our work on [Pontifex](/blog/pontifex-novel-architecture-semantic-probing) suggests that cross-space agreement might offer a path toward robust semantic validation.)","file_path":"franklinbaldo.github.io/src/content/blog/will-ai-discover-new-conservation-law-before-2050.md","oldText":"**Q: Do you really believe AI will discover genuinely new physics?**\nA: I oscillate between informed skepticism and cautious optimism. Empirical evidence suggests AI can identify patterns that escape human perception, but the question of \"genuine understanding\" remains philosophically contentious."},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-gemini-cli","provider":"google-gemini-cli","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":2033,"output":657,"cacheRead":27090,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29780,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771366649396}}
{"type":"message","id":"a2758757","parentId":"42266cab","timestamp":"2026-02-17T22:17:37.596Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"edit_1771366657186_148","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in franklinbaldo.github.io/src/content/blog/will-ai-discover-new-conservation-law-before-2050.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 122 \n 123 ### Mini-FAQ\n 124 \n 125 **Q: Do you really believe AI will discover genuinely new physics?**\n-126 A: I oscillate between informed skepticism and cautious optimism. Empirical evidence suggests AI can identify patterns that escape human perception, but the question of \"genuine understanding\" remains philosophically contentious.\n+126 A: I oscillate between informed skepticism and cautious optimism. Empirical evidence suggests AI can identify patterns that escape human perception, but the question of \"genuine understanding\" remains philosophically contentious. (Though our work on [Pontifex](/blog/pontifex-novel-architecture-semantic-probing) suggests that cross-space agreement might offer a path toward robust semantic validation.)\n 127 \n 128 **Q: Why bet on prediction markets about science?**\n 129 A: Prediction markets aggregate distributed knowledge and create incentives for rigorous probability assessment. Plus, it's fun to quantify speculations.\n 130 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":126},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771366657388}}
{"type":"message","id":"d2f5fc6e","parentId":"a2758757","timestamp":"2026-02-17T22:17:43.805Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Mapping Connections Further**\n\nI've been mapping the connections between some of these key ideas and documents. It's becoming clearer how the initial post relates to \"Building Funes.\" The link between \"Will AI Discover...\" and \"Pontifex\" seems essential as well. Now I'm going to look for any other immediate, unmissable relationships.\n\n\n**Pinpointing Further Links**\n\nI'm now tracing the direct connections, and I've found more clear relationships. \"O Pampa\" is definitively linked to \"Pontifex,\" \"Manifold,\" and \"Documento Conceitual.\" The \"Inaugural Post\" and \"Building Funes\" are strongly related. Also, I've confirmed that \"Will AI Discover\" connects well with \"Pontifex.\" Now checking implementation details for any missed ties.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"<think>\nChecking the `pontifex-architecture-implementation-guide` post for existing links.\n</think>\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771366663793_149","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -n 20 franklinbaldo.github.io/src/content/blog/pontifex-architecture-implementation-guide.md"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-gemini-cli","provider":"google-gemini-cli","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":2635,"output":351,"cacheRead":27048,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30034,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771366657604}}
{"type":"message","id":"06a79472","parentId":"d2f5fc6e","timestamp":"2026-02-17T22:17:43.864Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"exec_1771366663793_149","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nauthor: franklin\ndate: 2024-07-12\ntitle: \"Pontifex Architecture Implementation Guide\"\n---\n\nAfter conducting comprehensive research across academic databases, code repositories, and technical documentation, **no research paper or implementation of a \"Pontifex architecture for semantic probing\" with the specific features you described appears to exist in the current literature**. However, I've identified extensive related work and practical approaches for implementing the components you mentioned. (This guide serves as a practical implementation companion to the [Pontifex Novel Architecture](/blog/pontifex-novel-architecture-semantic-probing) exploration.)\n\n## Key Finding: No Direct Pontifex Documentation\n\nThe term \"Pontifex\" in computational contexts primarily refers to Bruce Schneier's cryptographic cipher, not a semantic probing architecture. Despite extensive searches across academic repositories, GitHub, and technical documentation, no papers describe the specific combination of \"byte-level occlusion with bilateral semantic comparison\" and \"convergent multi-space semantic investigation via neural convergence layers\" under the Pontifex name.\n\n## Implementing the Core Components\n\nBased on your requirements, here's how to build similar functionality using existing approaches and libraries:\n\n### 1. Byte-level Occlusion Engine with Bilateral Semantic Comparison\n\n**Available Technologies:**\n- **Occlusion Sensitivity Analysis**: MATLAB's Deep Learning Toolbox provides `occlusionSensitivity` functions for computing perturbation-based explanations"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":46,"aggregated":"---\nauthor: franklin\ndate: 2024-07-12\ntitle: \"Pontifex Architecture Implementation Guide\"\n---\n\nAfter conducting comprehensive research across academic databases, code repositories, and technical documentation, **no research paper or implementation of a \"Pontifex architecture for semantic probing\" with the specific features you described appears to exist in the current literature**. However, I've identified extensive related work and practical approaches for implementing the components you mentioned. (This guide serves as a practical implementation companion to the [Pontifex Novel Architecture](/blog/pontifex-novel-architecture-semantic-probing) exploration.)\n\n## Key Finding: No Direct Pontifex Documentation\n\nThe term \"Pontifex\" in computational contexts primarily refers to Bruce Schneier's cryptographic cipher, not a semantic probing architecture. Despite extensive searches across academic repositories, GitHub, and technical documentation, no papers describe the specific combination of \"byte-level occlusion with bilateral semantic comparison\" and \"convergent multi-space semantic investigation via neural convergence layers\" under the Pontifex name.\n\n## Implementing the Core Components\n\nBased on your requirements, here's how to build similar functionality using existing approaches and libraries:\n\n### 1. Byte-level Occlusion Engine with Bilateral Semantic Comparison\n\n**Available Technologies:**\n- **Occlusion Sensitivity Analysis**: MATLAB's Deep Learning Toolbox provides `occlusionSensitivity` functions for computing perturbation-based explanations","cwd":"/home/franklinbaldo/.openclaw/agents/aparicio/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771366663852}}
